timelineItems.text: That's what I love about Hector Jimenez at right back. He can serve in a great cross. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: That's the third #CrewSC road goal of the season in five-plus games.

timelineItems.name: Shane Forbes
timelineItems.text: Col scores. #ORLvCLB. They're an A team. They had 5 players in the box. Orlando still gets that part wrong, but they're improving.

timelineItems.name: Mike Tobin
timelineItems.text: #OCSC http://t.co/xL3C4WpNet

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Columbus controlling possession so far. #OCSC midfield getting overrun. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Allie Dosmann
timelineItems.text: Repping Crew SC tonight from Orlando! Crew draws first blood, 1-0 in the beginning of the first #CrewSC http://t.co/9B2Wv6H6LK

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Another corner for #OCSC. the left side combo of Boden and Rivas playing well on the attack

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Well this just got difficult. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Thomas Costello
timelineItems.text: Horrible card. Horrible. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: T.M. Jordy
timelineItems.text: That is a terrible call!!! What is parkhurst supposed to do?! His arms were down at his side! @ColumbusCrewSC #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Shannon
timelineItems.text: Confetti on the field #ORLvCLB http://t.co/Mx1VprbLKn

timelineItems.name: Alicia Rodriguez
timelineItems.text: Parkhurst had arm by his side, but it looks like he moves his arm to flick the ball away. I think it was a red card based on that. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Orlando City SC vs. Columbus Crew SC | May 30, 2015

timelineItems.name: Finolee Sinn
timelineItems.text: I love the contrast between #CrewSC's all-yellows and #OCSC's all-purples

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: Seems like Carlos Rivas still not in sync with his teammates yet. Understandable. Eric Avila has been phenomenal so far. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: FT: Exhale. Ribeiro's strike rescues a point for @OrlandoCitySC against #CrewSC --> http://t.co/RKJDDsQBVA #ORLvCLB http://t.co/yA5d74FOKE

timelineItems.name: Kelly Jo Larsen
timelineItems.text: Well when we subbed Higuain, I assumed we were going for the tie, so I suppose the point will do. Onward. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Columbus makes their first trip to the Citrus Bowl to face Orlando City.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Orlando City SC vs. Columbus Crew SC | May 30, 2015

timelineItems.name: ESPN 580
timelineItems.text: Larin with a great opportunity in the box, but he just can't get the shot off quick enough as Clark cut down the angle #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Stephan Sharp
timelineItems.text: Larin just handled the ball worse than Parkhurst did but Orlando just got a corner out of it. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: OhioTiger3
timelineItems.text: Pogatetz for MLS save of the week #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Weenie War Champ
timelineItems.text: Orlando City throwing up some nice pressure into that Crew box #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: #OCSC has Columbus pinned back and shouts go out for a penalty as Rivas takes a spill in the box, but the ref isn't having it. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 90 seconds in, Kei Kamara already tests Tally Hall. Good start for #CrewSC.

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: How about this shot from our photographer @nickleyvaphoto?! Kaká celebrates his goal with the fans! #ORLvCLB #OCSC http://t.co/fXD0mUG14Z

timelineItems.desc: Justin Meram (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Justin Meram sees yellow for hard foul

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: And now Meram's given a yellow for... stepping on someone's foot while making a challenge? I mean I guess... #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Well, witih Rivas in the lineup, #ocsc should increase their per game shot totals. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Shane Forbes
timelineItems.text: Man, again. Rivas is super selfish. Is he the most selfish player in the league? Luke had made a great run and was wide open. Pass. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Good job by Waylon to turn that #OCSC attack into a goal kick. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Keith Collette
timelineItems.text: That's some fine defending from Francis in his own corner. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: A bad giveaway by #OSCS is immediately negated by an equally bad giveaway by #CrewSC.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Despite the fact they have yet to get a non-PK goal, #OCSC has impressed me with how often they've gotten in the box. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Hector Jimenez (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Hector Jimenez takes down Rivas to earn the card

timelineItems.name: Austin Moore Farrow
timelineItems.text: The Crew really struggling since going down to 10 men. Not that that's surprising. OC just lacking that final ball atm. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: This is probably going to be the hottest game of the year for #CrewSC; will certainly test match fitness of all players. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Alicia Rodriguez
timelineItems.text: Tally Hall with the 'ol "Dad goalkeeper look" at the Citrus Bowl tonight. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Larry W. Johnson
timelineItems.text: Think early Higuain sub is b/c of surface. Don't want him covering all that ground for 10 man Crew for 70 mins. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Has anyone else seen Justin Meram been hit by loose balls struck after a whistle twice in this half? Or am I imagining it? #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Carlos Rivas (Orlando City SC) is shown the yellow card for simulation.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Carlos Rivas gets himself booked

timelineItems.name: Ben
timelineItems.text: Simulation yellow to Rivas. It should be his second, really. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: ValenciaVoice
timelineItems.text: HALFTIME: @OrlandoCitySC and Columbus are tied at 1-1 after the first 45 minutes. #ORLvCLB #MLS http://t.co/bx5bfdMyjm

timelineItems.name: Shane Forbes
timelineItems.text: Rivas should be subbed out. Has potential but weak. Selfish, now trying to cheat, at least a couple of times. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: I wouldn't say #CrewSC have their backs to the wall, but they've definitely got a head wind in the second half.

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Not sure I've heard Kevin Hartman's color commentary before this game. I have to say, I'm impressed. Good insights, balance #OCSC #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: While that was a rough half for #CrewSC, they need to focus on things they can control in the second: like bad turnovers in their own half.

timelineItems.name: saidulislam
timelineItems.text: Tony Chani should be removed. Can't dribble. Can't pass. Useless #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Tchani clearly the man of the match so far. Along w/ the goal he leads the team in pass usage rate and defensive actions. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Kristinn Steindorsson in for Justin Meram at the half. Justin was getting pretty heated. Might be preventing another red card... #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: Based on what we've seen out of his changes thus far, Berhalter is definitely looking ahead at Wednesday. #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Looks like everyone expected an offside call, including Rivas. #CrewSC #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Austin Moore Farrow
timelineItems.text: Steve Clark having a sturdy performance per usual. Save on Kaka earlier and huge save on Rivas there. Keeping the Crew in the game. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 0, Columbus Crew SC 1. Tony Tchani (Columbus Crew SC) header from the centre of the box to the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Tony Tchani heads in the opening goal for Columbus

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Great ball in. Not sure how it evaded so many #OCSC heads. #CrewSC clear it back into the other half.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Schmidt
timelineItems.text: Wow, Rivas really has to do better than that. Blows a big chance. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Mark A Pino
timelineItems.text: Really want to see Rivas score but I have a feeling the 'gaffer' will make some changes on offense soon. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: I know he's not the most popular guy within fan circles, but Tyson Wahl has really stepped it up tonight... he's needed to. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Kartik Krishnaiyer
timelineItems.text: Energy levels drop when you have to defend with 9 men for 75 minutes. Expect Columbus to wilt here and plus it's still humid. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: We need to get organized here. Playing way too close to goal. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: If the ref wanted to use a makeup call, he could there. But he didn't. good no-call. #CrewSC #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Becca Hanus
timelineItems.text: Orlando knows glitter. @OrlandoCitySC #ORLvCLB http://t.co/BsqZNMfAZy

timelineItems.name: Austin Moore Farrow
timelineItems.text: 31,430 tonight.. 36,587 home average attendance for #OCSC. Also means OC have 6 games over 30k. Pretty good for an expansion franchise. #MLS

timelineItems.name: molly jo
timelineItems.text: Every match I fall more & more in love with Pogatetz. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Purple Reign
timelineItems.text: 5' Tally Hall playing sweeper-keeper #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 1, Columbus Crew SC 2. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) header from the centre of the box to the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Kei Kamara's powerful header puts Columbus in front

timelineItems.name: Kartik Krishnaiyer
timelineItems.text: Against the run of play Kei Kamara the reigning #MLS POW with a great finish. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: What a ball by Waylon Francis, and Kamara with a powerful snap-header for his MLS-leading 10th goal of the year. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: Kei Kamara now has double-digit goals for the third time in his career. Leads the league with 10 in 12 games. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: With that goal, @keikamara becomes the fastest player in #CrewSC history to reach 10 goals (12 matches played).

timelineItems.name: Eli Ziegler
timelineItems.text: #OCSC http://t.co/ZWP2jxPQ2Y

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Waylon Francis led all MLS defenders in assists last year; you saw why with that cross he fed to Kamara. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew Marcinko
timelineItems.text: Orlando City shift to a 4-4-2 with Kaká out left and Paterson and Larin up top. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Clark has not been afraid to get his hops on tonight. #CrewSC #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Mauricio Rivas
timelineItems.text: #ORLvCLB I still say,don't like the Patterson guy.The referee whistles and the gusy still pushing and shoving on the other guy #Unbelievable

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Tell us how you really feel, @keikamara. #ORLvCLB http://t.co/fHqxsr8Lqy

timelineItems.name: kevin mercer
timelineItems.text: If you look at the field I think the Columbus Crew have nearly perfect spacing and positioning. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Oh god. Hope Francis is OK. We're out of subs. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Purple Reign
timelineItems.text: This is why #MLS needs goal-line technology - multiple replays makes it seem like the ball might have gone over in Clark's hands #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Jon Hiatt
timelineItems.text: The crew @OrlandoCitySC tonight. Let's get 3 points! #ORLvCLB http://t.co/Z31JqGCzKB

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: No Pogatetz in the #CrewSC XI probably due to busy upcoming schedule, and old man legs on turf. Rotation not a bad thing.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Clark snags a bouncing shot. #CrewSC have 10 minutes to hold on to their 10 man lead. 2-1 #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: #OCSC has only given up 3 goals once this year, to #CrewSC. Columbus hasn't given up more than 2, but has given up 2 six times (OC only 4x)

timelineItems.name: Orlando City Forum
timelineItems.text: The men responsible for it all. #ORLvCLB http://t.co/sfcBVerdOP

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Finlay starting tonight; broke his toe vs Chicago last week but appears to be over it; lineup pretty straight-forward for #CrewSC #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Poor Ramos, just not tall enough to defend the aerial game. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Assist from Hector Jimenez on the goal. As has been covered before, striking first is huge for #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew O'Brien
timelineItems.text: Brilliant dummy from Kaka there, but Larin with an awful hit. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.name: Carey Schumacher
timelineItems.text: Sorry @timbersarmy, you're cool but u don't have @orlandounicorn . @OrlandoCitySC #OCSC @thesdmatt http://t.co/Z5oWTmSqMr

timelineItems.name: Rob Del Medico
timelineItems.text: #OrlVClb http://t.co/xLA9jFXKOH

timelineItems.text: Here at the Orlando Citrus Bowl as #CrewSC checked-out the pitch earlier. Kickoff on @TWCSportsOH moments away. http://t.co/iwNbcOlNYd

timelineItems.name: Megan Myers
timelineItems.text: This whole "Brek Shea not playing" thing makes me anxious. Gah. #ORLvCLB

timelineItems.text: We hear it can get pretty loud in there. Make some noise for #ORLvCLB: http://t.co/qkWf0MMypZ http://t.co/Ay6d97qtVg

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #OCSC manager Adrian Heath refers to #CrewSC as one of the best teams in the league. Says they need all 11 players. #CrewSC

timelineItems.text: Ethan Finlay really getting it done for #CrewSC tonight.

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: It's a good thing there isn't much bite in this #OCSC attack, or #CrewSC could find themselves in a bad spot. Orlando wasteful with chances.

timelineItems.name: spot
timelineItems.text: No composure. Young team pressing and making mistakes. #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Berhalter said yesterday he's not worried about #CrewSC menatlity to close out games after last week's result. Big test here.

timelineItems.name: WrongSideOfThePond
timelineItems.text: Kamara and Finlay have put in some massive defensive shifts tonight. The former has been EVERYWHERE. #CrewSC #ORLvCLB
